  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\nThe apiserver does not clean up after itself when it does a controlled shutdown.  This means things like the internal kubernetes service endpoints still contain the ip information for an apiserver that no longer exists.  The system will eventually rectify the situation, but until that occurs there can still be service disruption (ie dns lookups) that need not occur.  If the apiserver goes through a controlled shutdown then it should clean up after itself, like de-registering from the internal kubernetes service.",
